'''Nikola Vasilj''' ({{IPA|hr|nǐkola ʋǎsiʎ|pron}}; born 2 December 1995) is a Bosnian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[2. Bundesliga]] club [[FC St. Pauli]] and the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina national team]].

Vasilj started his professional career at [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar]], who loaned him to [[FK Igman Konjic|Igman Konjic]] in 2014 and to [[HNK Branitelj|Branitelj]] in 2015. In 2017, he joined [[1. FC Nürnberg II]]. Two years later, he moved to [[FC Zorya Luhansk|Zorya Luhansk]]. He signed with FC St. Pauli in 2021.

A former youth international for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Vasilj made his senior international debut in 2021, earning over 20 [[Cap (sport)|caps]] since.

==Club career==

===Early career===
Vasilj started playing football at a local club, before joining the youth academy of his hometown team [[HŠK Zrinjski Mostar|Zrinjski Mostar]] in 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/vasilj-uskoro-cu-otkriti-zasto-je-vinko-marinovic-nekorektan-prema-mom-sinu-nikoli|title=Vasilj: Uskoro ću otkriti zašto je Vinko Marinović nekorektan prema mom sinu Nikoli|website=sportske.ba|date=18 August 2016|access-date=18 August 2016|language=bs}}</ref> He made his professional debut against [[FK Željezničar Sarajevo|Željezničar]] on 10 April 2013 at the age of 17.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/teska-povreda-zolotica-zrinjskom-bod-na-grbavici/102405|title=Teška povreda Zolotića, Zrinjskom bod na Grbavici|website=sportsport.ba|date=10 April 2013|access-date=11 April 2013|language=bs}}</ref> In July 2014, he was sent on a season-long loan to [[FK Igman Konjic|Igman Konjic]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/igman-se-pojacava/136170|title=Igman se pojačava|website=sportsport.ba|date=19 July 2014|access-date=22 July 2014|language=bs}}</ref> In July 2015, he was loaned to [[HNK Branitelj|Branitelj]] until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/branitelj-poceo-sa-pripremama-brojni-odlasci-i-dolasci/166506|title=Branitelj počeo sa pripremama, brojni odlasci i dolasci|website=sportsport.ba|date=5 July 2015|access-date=8 July 2015|language=bs}}</ref>

In July 2017, Vasilj signed with German side [[1. FC Nürnberg]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://oslobodjenje.ba/sport/fudbal/ino-fudbal/nikola-vasilj-potpisao-za-nurnberg-82316|title=Nikola Vasilj potpisao za Nürnberg|website=oslobodjenje.ba|date=1 July 2017|access-date=1 July 2017|language=bs}}</ref>

In July 2019, he joined Ukrainian outfit [[FC Zorya Luhansk|Zorya Luhansk]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/bivsi-golman-zrinjskog-karijeru-nastavlja-u-ukrajini/326168|title=Bivši golman Zrinjskog karijeru nastavlja u Ukrajini|website=sportsport.ba|date=16 July 2019|access-date=18 July 2019|language=bs}}</ref>

===FC St. Pauli===
In May 2021, Vasilj moved to [[FC St. Pauli]] on a three-year deal.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://faktor.ba/sport/fudbal/nikola-vasilj-karijeru-nastavlja-u-njemackoj/90466|title=Nikola Vasilj karijeru nastavlja u Njemačkoj|website=faktor.ba|date=24 May 2021|access-date=24 May 2021|language=bs}}</ref> He made his official debut for the team on 25 July against [[Holstein Kiel]] and kept a clean sheet.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/st-pauli-sigurnom-pobjedom-otvorio-sezonu-uspjesan-debi-vasilja/404403|title=St. Pauli sigurnom pobjedom otvorio sezonu, uspješan debi Vasilja|website=sportsport.ba|date=25 July 2021|access-date=28 July 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

In January 2024, he signed a new long-term contract with the squad.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/415565-nikola-vasilj-produzio-saradnju-sa-st-paulijem-direktor-i-trener-ga-posebno-hvalili|title=Nikola Vasilj produžio saradnju sa St. Paulijem, direktor i trener ga posebno hvalili|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=24 January 2024|access-date=24 January 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

Vasilj was an important piece in FC St. Pauli's conquest of the [[2023–24 2. Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga]] title, his first trophy with the club, which was sealed on 19 May and earned them promotion to the [[2024–25 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://n1info.ba/sport/nogomet/bh-reprezentativac-i-njegov-st-pauli-prvi-put-osvojili-2-bundesligu-navijaci-uletjeli-na-teren-video|title=Bh. reprezentativac i njegov St. Pauli prvi put osvojili 2. Bundesligu, navijači uletjeli na teren|website=n1info.ba|date=19 May 2024|access-date=22 May 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

He played his 100th game for the side against [[FC Augsburg]] on 15 September.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://reprezentacija.ba/439846-nikola-vasilj-branio-100-utakmicu-za-st-pauli|title=Nikola Vasilj branio 100. utakmicu za St. Pauli|website=reprezentacija.ba|date=15 September 2024|access-date=18 September 2024|language=bs}}</ref>

==International career==
Vasilj was a member of the [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national under-21 football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina under-21 team]] under coach [[Vlado Jagodić]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportsport.ba/fudbal/nikola-vasilj-naravno-da-imam-reprezentativne-ambicije-a-ukrajinska-liga-jaca-je-nego-ljudi-misle/369363|title=Nikola Vasilj: Naravno da imam reprezentativne ambicije a ukrajinska liga jača je nego ljudi misle|website=sportsport.ba|date=22 July 2020|access-date=22 July 2020|language=bs}}</ref>

In March 2021, he received his first senior call up, for [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification – UEFA Group D|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifiers]] against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] and [[France national football team|France]] and a [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] game against [[Costa Rica national football team|Costa Rica]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://avaz.ba/sport/nogomet/636793/petev-objavio-spisak-za-martovske-utakmice-jedno-novo-ime|title=Petev objavio spisak za martovske utakmice, jedno novo ime|website=avaz.ba|date=11 March 2021|access-date=11 March 2021|language=bs}}</ref> He debuted against Costa Rica on 27 March.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/bih-i-dalje-bez-pobjede-remi-sa-kostarikom-na-bilinom-polju|title=BiH i dalje bez pobjede: Remi sa Kostarikom na Bilinom Polju|website=sportske.ba|date=27 March 2021|access-date=28 March 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

In June 2026, Vasilj was named in Bosnia and Herzegovina's squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sportske.ba/clanak/barbarez-poslao-konacan-spisak-fifa-i-jedno-ime-otputovalo-u-ameriku-ali-nije-na-listi|title=Barbarez poslao konačan spisak FIFA-i: Jedno ime otputovalo u Ameriku, ali nije na listi|website=sportske.ba|date=3 June 2026|access-date=3 June 2026|language=bs}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Vasilj's father [[Vladimir Vasilj|Vladimir]] was also a goalkeeper, as is his younger brother Filip.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://hercegovina.info/sport/nogomet/vratarska-obitelj-vasilj-filip-ponajbolji-vratar-prve-lige-kuca-na-vrata-mlade-reprezentacije-169676|title=Vratarska obitelj Vasilj: Filip ponajbolji vratar Prve lige, kuca na vrata mlade reprezentacije|website=hercegovina.info|date=9 September 2019|access-date=11 September 2019|language=hr}}</ref>

He married his long-time girlfriend Sara in May 2021.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://klix.ba/sport/nogomet/u-citluku-se-ozenio-golman-zmajeva-nikola-vasilj/210527154|title=U Čitluku se oženio golman Zmajeva Nikola Vasilj|website=klix.ba|date=27 May 2021|access-date=28 May 2021|language=bs}}</ref>

